div.div: defining "the user is not watching" is difficult to be honest, the user might tab out for it to buffer etc

you can go to settings and reduce the download speed to something under your max internet connection i do not want an option of "pause torrent" as it exposes the torrents too much to the user, making him worry about it one of the design principles of this app is to abstract away torrents as much as possible, so the user can use the app without even knowing it uses torrents

This is something widely outside of my reach too, i recommend you set the home screen releases RSS to erai [via settings], and disable "auto play torrents" in rss settings, then look for erai/multi-sub releases, but finding multi-sub releases isnt always easy, and they dont exist for all torrents
